  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0bb0\u0bae\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0bb5\u0bc7\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0 \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc7\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bca\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0ba4\u0bc0\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b8e\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b8e\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc7\u0ba9\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc7\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b89\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0ba4\u0bbe? - \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bae\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc7\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bbf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Does anyone doubt that our decision to prevent Ranil Wickremesinghe from becoming an Acting President was correct? - Sumandran's question",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "Does anyone now have any doubt that the decision taken by the Tamil Tesiya Federation to prevent the election of Ranil Wickramasinghe as the Executive President of Podujana Peramuna and to take the necessary efforts for it is correct? The media spokesperson of the Federation of Tamil Tessia and Member of Parliament for Yallam District has asked President's Attorney MA Sumanthran.",
        "Called 'Kota Ko Kama' in front of the Presidential Secretariat in Colombo's Kalimughat, the self-insurgency that had been going on for more than 100 days in a very vigorous manner by the public has subsided to some extent with the resignation of former President Gotabaya Rajapaksa.",
        "However, following the inauguration of the new President, Ranil Wickramasinghe, on Friday 22nd midnight, the Presidential Secretariat was surrounded by three forces and the 'Kota Ko Kama' protesters were dispersed from there. Meanwhile, the videos of the soldiers and Special Action Force severely attacking the protesters, the lawyers who had visited there to investigate the situation and appear on behalf of the arrested protesters, and the journalists who were engaged in their work, were widely shared on social media.",
        "Following this, MA Sumanthran, Member of Parliament of Jaffna District of Tamil Tesiya Federation has made a post on his official Twitter page, in which he has raised the following question.",
        "'Does anyone now have any doubt that the decision taken by the Tamil Tesiya Federation to prevent the election of Ranil Wickramasinghe as the executive president of the PDP and to take the necessary steps is correct?' He has questioned that.",
        "Similarly, Sumanthran, who made a post quoting the photo of lawyer Samara Jayasinghe, who was badly beaten by the soldiers in Kalimukhatital area on Friday midnight, pointed out that the lawyer was in her professional dress and said that 'this is how Ranil Wickramasinghe and the Podujana Peramuna government is giving lawyers the opportunity to meet the arrested people'."
      ],
